00:18:41.880 --> 00:18:44.099
I mean, paste would work just the same, right?

00:18:44.099 --> 00:18:46.199
If you like paste, use paste.

00:18:46.199 --> 00:18:49.479
But I find this very easy to read.

00:18:49.479 --> 00:18:53.599
These curly braces are very low overhead, right?

00:18:53.599 --> 00:18:57.880
So it's very easy to just look at the piece of text that comes out and says, yes, this

00:18:57.880 --> 00:19:03.640
looks correct, versus with paste, it gets a bit more complicated to figure out what

00:19:03.640 --> 00:19:07.079
the final output actually will be.

